# Cloudflare Pages _redirects.
#
# CF Pages's status-200 rewrite is same-domain only — a cross-origin
# target silently falls through to the SPA catch-all, which is why our
# Lightning address broke until this was changed to a 302. The LNURL
# callback URL in the response is already api.deepmarks.org, so step 2
# of the LNURL-pay flow never touches the apex again; the one 302 hop
# on step 1 is fine for modern wallets (Alby, Zeus, Phoenix, Damus,
# Cash App, etc. all follow redirects on well-known).
/.well-known/lnurlp/* https://api.deepmarks.org/.well-known/lnurlp/:splat 302
